            <fr:title text="Euclidean Space">Euclidean Space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
    The <html:strong>Euclidean space</html:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:link href="/gtop-0003/" title="Metric Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0003/" display-uri="gtop-0003" type="local">metric space</fr:link> equipped with the Euclidean metric
</html:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[d(x, y) = \lVert  x - y \rVert  = \sqrt {\sum _{i=1}^{n} (x_i - y_i)^2}]]></fr:tex>
            <html:p>
    The <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topology</fr:link> induced by this metric is called the <html:strong>standard topology</html:strong> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex>. In this topology, the <fr:link href="/gtop-000S/" title="Open Ball" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000S/" display-uri="gtop-000S" type="local">open ball</fr:link> centered at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> with radius <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon  > 0]]></fr:tex> is
</html:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[B(x, \epsilon ) = \left \{ y \in  \mathbb {R}^n : \lVert  y - x \rVert  < \epsilon  \right \}]]></fr:tex>
            <html:p>
    This is a special case of a <fr:link href="/gtop-0003/" title="Metric Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0003/" display-uri="gtop-0003" type="local">metric space</fr:link>, which in turn induces a <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topological space</fr:link>.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
